LANGUAGE STRUCTURED GEOMETRY 
============================================================
Including special topics (e.g., bilingualism, multilingualism)
Class here interdisciplinary works on language and literature

0. GLOBAL RDG ORIENTATION
============================================================
Geometry of Linguistic Objects

TIER A: META-LANGUAGE
    - Operators governing meaning, reference, pragmatics, terminology,
      acquisition, psycholinguistic dynamics.

TIER B: OBJECT-LANGUAGE
    - Operators governing structure of actual languages: phonology,
      morphology, syntax, writing systems, dialects, historical change.

RDG VIEW:
    SID = Structure–Interaction–Dynamics of linguistic classes
    PED = Power–Evaluation–Dynamics when applied to real artifacts
    RDG-mode = Semantic / Syntactic / Historical / Applied geometry

